abstract: House Select Committee on Benghazi issues final report finding no proof of culpability by Hillary Clinton in 2012 attacks in Benghazi, Libya, ending protracted and costly inquiry; report also rebukes Obama administration and various government agencies for missteps, but lack of clear finding of professional misconduct is likely to fuel criticisms of investigation and Republicans who led committee.
lead_paragraph: Ending one of the longest, costliest and most bitterly partisan congressional investigations in history, the Select Committee on Benghazi issued its report.

headline.main: House Benghazi Report Finds No New Evidence of Wrongdoing by Hillary Clinton
headline.print_headline: Benghazi Panel Finds No Misdeeds by Clinton
